CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1782436704
OL,3,CAmbulance chief warns people to 'drink
OL,4,Cresponsibly' as sweltering heat
OL,5,Ccontinues
OL,7,FA yellow warning is in place for
OL,8,Fthunderstorms for south-west England
OL,9,Fon Thursday night, while swathes of
OL,10,FScotland, England, Wales and Northern
OL,11,FIreland face yellow warnings for
OL,12,Fthunderstorms on Friday.
OL,14,FAnnie Shuttleworth, a Met Office
OL,15,Fmeteorologist, said lightning is
OL,16,Flikely on Thursday night for some
OL,17,Fareas in the South West, with rain in
OL,18,Fmore northern areas on Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1782436704
OL,3,CAmbulance chief warns people to 'drink
OL,4,Cresponsibly' as sweltering heat
OL,5,Ccontinues
OL,7,FEastern England is expected to see the
OL,8,Fhighest temperatures on Friday, she
OL,9,Fadded, but things will "finally cool
OL,10,Fdown this weekend".
OL,12,FWales has seen its hottest June day on
OL,13,Frecord on Thursday, with 35.9C
OL,14,Frecorded in Cardiff, meanwhile,
OL,15,FNorthern Ireland has seen the previous
OL,16,Frecord high for June matched after a
OL,17,Ftemperature of 30.8C was reached in
OL,18,FCastlederg.
OL,26,@qD@XOUrD@RO]
